Key Match Events: Damian Lillard finished with 41 points, four rebounds, and nine assists.
Lillard went 13-for-24 from the field, including 10-for-15 from beyond the arc.
Lillard hit the go-ahead jump shot with 9.8 seconds left to give the Bucks the lead.
Donovan Mitchell made the game-winning shot with 0.3 seconds remaining to secure a 114-113 win for the Cavaliers.
Post-Match Reflections: Damian Lillard's 41-point effort was wasted as the Milwaukee Bucks suffered their fifth-straight defeat.
The Bucks will need to play much better to get out of their losing streak as they face the Cavaliers again on Monday.
